Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 751 Filed 08/10/22 Page 232 of 261 1393
LC6Cmax7 Maguire - cross
1 right?
2 A. Yes, sir.
3 Q. That's a quarter of a century; right?
4 A. Yes, sir.
5 Q. And, in addition to what the house generally looked like in that earlier time period of the 1990s, say, those photographs we looked at don't show what items were in the house at that time period, necessarily, do they?
6 A. Again, I would not have any personal knowledge of that.
7 Q. Those photographs wouldn't necessarily show what furnishings were in the house in the 1990s and the 2000s; right?
8 A. Again, I don't know if it's representative or not.
9 Q. And those photographs wouldn't necessarily show what artwork was on the walls in that time period that I'm talking about; right?
10 A. Again, I don't know if it represents that or not.
11 Q. Bottom line is that these photographs really show what it looked like at the time of the search in 2019?
12 A. That's the day that I was there, yes.
13 Q. So you also mentioned that the search began around -- I guess you said 6:30 is when the search began --
14 A. Actually 6:15.
15 Q. 6:15?
16 A. Yes, sir.
SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
DOJ-OGR-00018569
